{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254693/1930040301/0129.xml":{"full_text":"UNRULY YOUTHS\nBRO w\nU. S. W\nV. 8. 8. TENNESSEE, April 3\n(IJJBJ.\u2014The days when wild\nboys were sent to the Navy to\nbe reformed are over.\nPhysical, mental and moral\nstandards have been raised.\nBoys who return to ship after\nshore leave are carefully looked\nover by a husky sergeant-at-arms.\nIf they are intoxicated they are\nsent to the brig (jail) and come\nbefore the captain at \u201cmast\u201d the\nnext morning. \"Mast\u201d is the\nlower or discipline court of the\nship.\nBad Boys Barred\nIt is not generally known on\nland that the Navy will not allow\nbad boys to remain in service.\nDue to the present selective\nmethod of obtaining men, the\nnumber of desertions decreased\nfrom approximately 7,000 yearly\nin past years to 450 last year.\nMen for the navy are recruited\nfrom five areas, which cover the\nUnited States. After the applica\ntion is signed the applicant is not\ntaken into the service immediate\nly. A confidential report is ob\ntained from his last school teacher\nand last employer. In addition,\nhe must measure up to certain\nphysical and mental requirements.\nIncreased thoroughness at recruit\ning stations has materially reduced\nthe number of misfits.\nTaught Discipline\nAt the training stations the en\nlisted men are taught to forget\nthey are civilians. They are in\nstructed in obedience, deportment,\nhygiene, care of person and\nclothes. There also follows an\naptitude and intelligence test.\nOnce in the Navy, it is possible\nfor a youth who has had a high\nschool education to rise to the\nhighest rank, that of admiral, al\nthough there is at present no ad\nmiral who has come up from\nranks.\nFAirBUSINESS\nABROAD SEEN\nAmerican foreign trade in 1930\nwill not reach the nearly $lO\n000,000,000 figure of last year,\nbut the present situation is not\ndevoid of encouraging features.\nDr. Julius Klein. Assistant Secre\ntary of Commerce, said today.\nIn the settlement of the repara\ntions problem through the Young\nplan, and the anticipated recov\nery of business in United States.\nKlein sees hope of improvement\nin export and import trade from\nthe declines noticed in the first\nthree months of the year.\nThe slump in foreign trade has\nbeen the result of a world-wide\nsag in commerce and industry\nfollowing the extraordinary activ\nity of 1929, with a combination\nof other economic and political\nfactors which have caused busi\nness to suffer. On a sliding down\nof prices there has been the\nnatural tendency to hold goods\noff the market, a development\nwhich will correct itself when\nthere is a turn in the price trend,\naccording to Klein.\nU. S. Trade Aids World\nA business revival in United\nStates would be of great impor\ntance to international trade, since\nthe business of all the world is\nto a considerable degree contin\ngent on American purchasing\npower. If this strengthens, as\nanticipated, through the presi\ndent\u2019s construction program, the\nworld will benefit.\nMan; of the \u201cone product\ncountries in Latin America and\nelsewhere have suffered. Tn Cuba\nsugar prices have been down,\nColombia and Brazil have suffered\nfrom the ccffee situation, Vene\nzuela and Mexico as the result of\noil prica falls, and Japan from\nsilk declines in India and China,\nlarge potential markets for Ameri\ncan machinery and other finished\nproducts, political uncertainty has\ndepressed buying.\nPlans Valuable\n\"However, exporters who have\nfor many years maintained agen\ncies abroad, are not suffering\ngreatly,\u201d Klein said. \u201cThis shows\nthe value of long distance plann\ning in the export field.\nWHOLE FUNERAL\nComplete, SIOO !ars and All\nCaskets Any Color Desired\nCemetery Plot as Low as S4O\nWe Claim That We Produce the Finest\nEconomical Funeral in the World\n/n Case of Death\nA Sincere Siruiet By\nThe Greater CHAMBERS c..\nOffices and Chapels, 14th Cor. Chapin N. W.\nPhone Columbia 0432\njSAouZcZ tAe Tofee ~to_ the Wister\nLll\nly\n\u00bb\u00bb'.51 Vii i ill Ai\n\nt \u2014Photo 'by International\nCREW INSPECTS 12 GIANT ENGINES OF CRAFT\nIF ON ITS MAIDEN TRIP across the Atlantic Ocean, this summer, via the Azores,\nthe flying boat DO-X should be compelled to take to the water during a period out\nfor repairs, the passengers will not be endangered. The ship will act quite like a well\nbehaved ocean liner. Fifty passengers are expected to make the historic trip. _\nTRAFFIC LIGHTS\nFOR BETHESDA\nBETHESDA. Md.. Apr 1 3.\u2014The\nwork of installing the new traffic\ncontrol lights at two heavily\ntraveled Intersections here and\nat Silver Spring is expected to\nget under way immediately.\nThe new lights will be installed\nhere near the Bank of Bethesda,\nand where the Bethesda-Chevy\nChase-Silver Spring highway in\ntersects Wisconsin Avenue, Old\nGeorgetown Road and Edgemoor\nLane.\nOfficials state that traffic regu\nlation by light is admittedly dif\nficult at this point due to the\nfact that the highways forming\nthe intersection do not cross at\nright angles, but provide a five\npoint intersection, aggravated by\nthe fact that one of the main\nhighways\u2014the Old Georgetown\nRoad\u2014and the electric trolleys\nmake a left-hand turn.\nAt Silver Spring, the lights\nwill be installed at the intersec\ntion of Georgia Avenue with the\nColesville Road and the new Be\nthesda-Chevy Chase-Silver Spring\nhighway.\n\u201cWild Pigeons\u201d Damage\nRanches in California\nBAKERFIELD, Calif., April 3\n(IN.S.) .\u2014Thousands of pigeons,\nidentified by local people as \u201cwild\npigeons\u201d are migrating from the\nhigh mountains and damaging\nranches in the Arvin and Weed\npatch districts.\nThe true wild pigeon, once com\nparable with the buffalo as a\nteeming form of American wild\nlife, has been exterminated, ex\nperts claim.\nAn airplane was employed to\nfly through the pigeon flocks to\nkeep them on the move.\nThe state game and fish com\nmission plans to send investiga\ntors to map a plan for removing\nthe pigeons as a menace to crops.\nA CLEAR COMPLEXION\nRuddy cheeks\u2014sparkling eyes\u2014\nmost women can have. Dr. F. M.\nEdwards for 20 years treated scores\nof women for liver and bowel ail\nments. During these years he gave\nhis patients a substitute for calomel\nmade of a few well-known vegetable\ningredients, naming them Dr. Ed\nwards Olive Tablets. Know them\nbv their olive color.\nThese tablets are wonder-workers\non the liver and bowels, causing a\nnormal action carrying off the\nwaste and poisonous matter in one\u2019s\nsystem.\nIf you have a pale face, sallow\nlook, dull eyes, pimples, coated\ntongue, headaches, a listless, no\ngood feeling, all out of sorts, inac\ntive bowels. take one of Dr. Ed\nwards Olive Tablets nightly for a\ntime and note the pleasing results\nThousands of women and men\ntake Dr. Edwards Olive Tablets\nnow and then to keep fit. 18c. 30c\nand 60c.\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES\nCOSGRAVEBACK\nUS PRESIDENT\nDUBLIN. April 3 (1.N.5.).\u2014\nWilliam T. Cosgrave returned to\nday to the presidency of the\nIrish Free State executive council,\nhis policies vindicated and his\nposition stronger than at any\ntime since he first took office in\n1922.\nAfter nine hours of debate and\nfollowing the rejection of the can\ndidacies of his two strongest\nopponents, Eamonn De Valera\nand Thomas J. O\u2019Connell, Cos\ngrave yesterday was reelected by\nthe Dail Eireann by a vote of\n80 to 65.\nCosgrave had resigned after the\nDail had favored, by two votes,\na bill to extend old-age pensions,\na measure the President had op\nposed because it would cause too\ngreat a drain on the country\u2019s\nfinances.\nCosgrave was expected today to\nsubmit to the Dail names of the\nsame men who were with him in\nthe old cabinet.\nWriter Reports New\nBreed of Dog in Ita\u2019y\nNEW YORK, April 3.\u2014A\nstrange, ferocious dog, as large as\na Great Dane, with the head of\nSt. Bernard, the forelegs and\nshoulders of a bulldog, and the\ncurly red mane of a retriever, is\nreported by Albert Payson Ter\nhune, who breeds dogs and\nwrites about them.\nHe returned from Italy in the\nLloyd Sabaudo liner Conte Blan\ncamano,. He said of his find:\n\u201cIt is something a man would\nexpect to -see when drunk.\u201d\nPrevented by the natives from\ntaking his curiosity away, Ter\nhune said he is going to return\nnext year and make another at\ntempt.\nNote this\nVALUE/\nCLICQUOT CLUB\nPALE DRY OFFERS\nl /3 more for your money\nBWJERE\u2019S away to eave money\nA A when you buy ginger ale.\nSimply askjor Clicquot Club Palo\nDry. It cornea In full IS-ounce pint\nbottles, not scanty 12-ounce bottle/\nlike you usually got. Clicquot gives\nyou 4 extra ounces In every bottle.\nAnd to insure its purity this famous\naged ginger ale comes to you in\ndean new bottles. Bottles that have\nThis rlcM sAews Aew\nm.\u00abA yee ft in bwors-\n\u2022eery Sets h \u00bbf CUcft\nCM Pels Dry.\nThe handy party |-fl| <TT4lm\npackage containing\n12 full pints.\nTHIS BARGAIN OFFERED\nAT YOUR STORE TODAY\n\nProfessional Begging\nDignified in Madrid\nMADRID, April 3 (1.N.8.).\u2014\nBeggars can still be choosers in\nMadrid. They will accept your\npennies but throw away your\nbread.\nThe city authorities have just\nopened a park for them and thev\ncan now elect to ply their trade\nfurtively in the streets or with\ndraw temporarily into dignified\nretirement. The world\u2019s greatest\ngamble, the Spanish lottery, was\ninvented to keep and comfort\nthose who could or would not\nwork.\n\nSloan\u2019s\nLiniment\nDeaf Hear Again\nThrough New Ai\nEarpiece No Bigger Than Din:\nWins Enthusiastic Following\nTen-Day Free Trial Offer\nAfter twenty-five years devoted exclu\nsively to the manufacture of scientit\nhearing-aids, the Dictograph Product\nCo.. Inc.. Dept. 314 M, 220 West 42->\nStreet, New York. N. T has just pet\nfected a new model Acouatocon that rep\nresents the greatest advance yet made\nIn the re-creation of hearing for th'\ndeaf. This latest Acoustlcon Is feature.!\nbv a tiny earpiece no bigger than x\ndime. Through this device sounds are\nclearly and distinctly transmitted to sub\nnormal ears with wonderful benefit t<-\nhearing and health alike. The makers\noffer an absolutely free trial for 10 day,\nto any person who may be Interested\nand a letter will bring one of these re\nmarkable aids to home for a thorough\nand convincing test. Send them your\nname and address today!\nA free demonstration may be had a'\nthe Washington Office of the Dictograph\nProducts Co.. Room #OO. National Press\nBldg.. 14th and F Sts N. W.\nThe National Daily\nNEW RULE AIDS\nAIR STUDENTS\nLOS ANGELES, April 3 (1.N.5.).\nForeign students desiring to enter\nthe United States to attend recog\nnized flying schools will not have\nto wait on immigration quotas\nhereafter, according to s a far\nreaching ruling made by the Fed\neral Commissioner\u2019General of Im\nmigration.\nThe ruling was invoked in the\nrecognition of the Curtiss-Wright\nFlying Service School here, giving\nit the same \u2019footing as a uni\nversity in the matter of accept\ning foreign students hot regularly\nentered through the Immigration\nchannels.\nHeretofore, the school has re\nceived many applications for ad\nmission from foreigners desirous\nof studying aviation here, only to\nbe forced to refuse them because\nthe immigration ruling did not ad\nmit nonquota foreigners to study\nin the air school, according to\nMajor C. C. Mosely.\nBritain Appeals to Save\nSea Birds From Oil\nCAMBRIDGE, England, April 3.\nThe attention of the League of Na\ntions was called by the Students\u2019\nCongress to the destruction of sea\nbirds by the discharge of oil waste\nfrom tankers all over the world.\nThe oil floats on the surface, and\nevery sea bird touching it has its\nwings coated and perishes, they\npointed out.\nH. de Vere Stacpoole. the novel\nist, said that the death of a sea\nbird from this cause is \u201cthe most\nterrible thing invented by the\ndevil.\u201d\nA cup of noble Coffee\ndrew them to _ _\nNi \u202211 _. m WHiimmS\nas n v 111 e MB wBHsB\nI1 IFI w||M|S|lSlj\nIt was only natural that in the days of the Old Q\nSouth, people of wealth-and leisure should in- jg M wB Willi\nelude Nashville in their travels, and dine at the 11\nold Maxwell House \u2014for of all the fine hotels of 1 11' 1 mMrIiI\nDixie, this was the most famed. I HUM BHI\nerHh\nEspecially was its fragrant coffee a celebrated\nand tempting attraction\u2014the high grace note of J |WS|I| I\nan epicurean cuisine.\nSo rich and satisfying was its aroma, so rare\nand mellow its flavor, that each year this special\nblend has been sought by more and more people. j1\nToday Maxwell House Coffee is prized in millions I HI WJ\nof homes. There is only one Mend of Maxwell ll| SI :|i 111 11|| jSjA\nHouse Coffee. Why don\u2019t you try it tomorrow? I I II H\\ *l] |U\nThe quality that has made it famous is always the ijvgk\nsame and there is always the same net weight of '\u2019l|| I IJBSI\ncoffee as specified on the friendly blue tin, no I\nmatter where or from whom you buy it. You can B I\ntry Maxwell House Coffee without risk of dis- \u2018l|||\nappointment\u2014if you are not fully satisfied, your x*.\ngrocer will unhesitatingly return your money. good%=4\n(the' v\ndR WB LAST\nDROP\nmii XIAJSIwm\nlIKIJ Vll /Mffy Don\u2019t miss the Maxwell House\nTil '3k I /rn^KR L radio program every Thursday\nLH V Clwir\" M f I WK& lif evening, at 9:30, Eastern Stand-\nfin IBy V< WPn ard Time. Broadcast from VTJZ\nililli rJ I 9a Uu'i in N. Y. C over the National\nI I Broadcasting coast-to-eoast\nJ M vy- hook-up.\nMaxwell House\nI fITTPP Afndua.l\n\\jlf ts VW -GENERAL POODS CORPORATION\nI9J\u00ae. 0 F- Cor>. i\n\nTHURSDAY, APRIL 3, 1930\nTRAINING GAMP\nBOOKS OPEN\nEnrollment in the citizens mili\ntary training camps has begun\ntoday, and a concerted effort is\nbeing made by the local procure\nment committee to fill the Dis\ntrict\u2019s quota of 307 men. In past\nyears Washington filled or sur\npassed her quota in the early\ndays of the enrollment. Young\nmen between the ages of 17 and\n21 are eligible to attend the\ncamps, which are located in all\nparts of the country and were\nestablished under the national\ndefense act.\nWashington boys will be sent\nto the following camps: Fort\nEustis, Va.; Fort Hoyle, Md.; Fort\nMonroe. Va.; Fort Myer, Va., and\nFort Monmouth, N. J.\nApplication for enrollment\nshould be made at the organized\nreserves headquarters, Oxford\nBuilding, Fourteenth Street and\nPennsylvania Avenue.\nCity or aaborban homo offering yon\nmany long-wanted pleoanrea are Uated\ntor ante in Time. Claealfled Ada.\ni CREERON\nB 614 Twelfth Street\na Small Headtizet\n\u25a0S Trimmed and\nTailored HATS\ns 3= and 5\nA carefully selected group of\nHata in amall head-aizes. Most\n\u25a0F unusual values; 20 Styles\u2014lo\nw colors to choose from.\nTALKS ABOUT EAGLES\nDr. Francis H. Herrick, pro\nfessor of biology in Adelbert Col\nlege, Western Reserve University,\nwill address members of the Na\ntional Geographic Society at the\nWashington Auditorium tomorrow\nevening on \"The Eagle in Action.\"\nADVERTISEMENT\nNew Kind of Salts\nTaking Country By Storm\nThey Revitalize the System\u2014lnduce Youthful Ac\ntivity\u2014Keep Body In Splendid Condition\nFree From Fat.\nIt doesn\u2019t take long for Ameri\ncans to wake up to a good thing\n\u2014only a few months ago Krus\nchen Salts were introduced into\nthis country and the welcome\nnews of their superior goodness\nand swift rejuvenating power\ntraveled so fast that at one time\nthe supply was many carloads\nbehind the demand.\nAll of which goes to prove that\nAmericans know good salts when\nthey take them and want their\nfriends to benefit also.\nKruschen Salts are taken for\ntheir health building value all\nover the world\u2014they are the larg\nest selling medicinal salts in\nGreat Britain today.\nKruschen Salts are different\nfrom other salts \u2014Kruschen is six\nsalts in one\u2014the very same six\nsalts that nature put into the\nhuman body at the beginning of\ncreation and demands you keep\nthem there or your health won\u2019t\nbe as good as it should be.\nUnlike most salts Kruschen isn\u2019t\nsimply a laxative\u2014if that\u2019s all\nHIGHLAND CITIZENS MEET\nThe Highland Citizens Associa\ntion will be addressed by Repre\nsentative Simmons, of Nebraska,\nat the meeting Monday night in\nthe assembly room of the Sixth\nPresbyterian Church at Sixteenth\nand Kendedy Streets Northwest.\nADVERTISEMENT\nyou want any old kind of salts\nwith any kind of a label will de\nbut is that all you want?\nWhen you take Kruschen Salts\nyou not only stimulate your\nbowels, liver and kidneys to func\ntion naturally and perfectly, but\nyou supply every internal drgan,\ngland, nerve and fibre in the\nbody with nature\u2019s own revitaliz\ning and rejuvenating minerals.\nA bottle of Kruschen Salts that\nlasts 4 weeks costs but 85c st\nPeoples Drug Stores or any drug\nstore in America\u2014take one half\na teaspoon in a glass of hot water\nevery morning before breakfast\nin just a few days indolence\nchanges to activity and life grows\nbrighter.\nBefore the bottle is empty you\u2019ll\nfeel years younger\u2014eyes will\nbrighten\u2014step grow sprightlier\u2014\nnerves steadier\u2014you\u2019ll sleep sound,\nenjoy your meals and after a\nhard day\u2019s work you\u2019ll be ready\nfor wholesome recreation\u2014one\nmillion Americans know all this\u2014\nask your druggist.\n23","height":"30507","width":"24201"}}
